# NeRF â€” 3D Scene Reconstruction

Implements Neural Radiance Fields (NeRF) on the NeRF Synthetic Chair dataset.

## Setup

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Place chair images in `data/nerf_chair_images/` (download from [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/nguyenhung1903/nerf-synthetic-dataset)).

## Run

```bash
python nerf_reconstruction.py
```

## Outputs (saved to `outputs/`)

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| `sample_images.png` | Dataset preview grid |
| `training_loss.png` | Training loss curve |
| `novel_views.png` | Synthesised novel views |
| `psnr_ssim_evaluation.png` | PSNR & SSIM bar charts |
| `nerf_model.pth` | Saved model weights |